INSERT INTO comprension_texts (subject_id, level, grades, title, text_content, questions) VALUES
('ingles','eso','{3}','The Importance of Recycling',
'Recycling is one of the most effective ways to protect our planet. Every day, people around the world produce huge amounts of waste, and most of it ends up in landfills or in the ocean. This causes serious damage to the environment and to wildlife. Recycling helps to reduce this problem because materials like paper, glass, plastic, and metal can be transformed into new products instead of being thrown away. For example, a recycled aluminium can saves enough energy to power a television for three hours. In many European countries, citizens are used to separating their rubbish into different containers: blue for paper, yellow for plastic and cans, green for glass, and brown for organic waste. Schools also play an important role by teaching children about the three Rs: Reduce, Reuse, and Recycle. Although recycling is essential, experts say it is not enough. We must also try to consume less and choose products with less packaging. Everyone, from governments to ordinary citizens, has a responsibility to take care of our planet.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Qué se ahorra al reciclar una lata de aluminio?","opciones":["Agua para una hora","Energía para encender una televisión durante tres horas","Plástico","Papel"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿De qué color es el contenedor del plástico en muchos países europeos?","opciones":["Azul","Amarillo","Verde","Marrón"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué son las tres erres?","opciones":["Reducir, Reutilizar y Reciclar","Recoger, Recolectar y Reutilizar","Reciclar, Repetir y Recordar","Renovar, Reciclar y Reciclar"],"correcta":0},{"pregunta":"¿Qué dicen los expertos además del reciclaje?","opciones":["Que basta con reciclar","Que debemos consumir menos y elegir productos con menos envase","Que no sirve de nada","Que solo los gobiernos deben actuar"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','British Tea Culture',
'Tea is much more than a drink in the United Kingdom: it is a true cultural tradition. The British have been drinking tea since the seventeenth century, when it was first imported from China and India. Today, the average British person drinks about three cups of tea per day. There are tea breaks at work, and many people start the morning with a cup of strong black tea with milk. The most famous tea moment is "afternoon tea", a tradition started in the 1840s by the Duchess of Bedford. She often felt hungry between lunch and dinner, so she asked her servants to bring her tea, sandwiches, and cakes in the late afternoon. Soon, this custom became fashionable among the upper classes and later spread to the rest of the population. Today, having afternoon tea in a fancy hotel in London is a popular activity for tourists. The menu usually includes small sandwiches without crusts, scones with jam and cream, and a variety of cakes. Even though coffee has become popular in recent years, tea remains an essential part of British identity and daily life.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Cuántas tazas de té bebe de media un británico al día?","opciones":["Una","Dos","Tres","Cinco"],"correcta":2},{"pregunta":"¿Quién inició la tradición del té de la tarde?","opciones":["La reina Victoria","La duquesa de Bedford","Una sirvienta","Un cocinero famoso"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué se sirve normalmente en el té de la tarde?","opciones":["Hamburguesas","Sandwiches sin corteza, scones con mermelada y nata, y pasteles","Pizza","Sopa"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué representa el té para los británicos?","opciones":["Solo una bebida","Una parte esencial de su identidad","Una moda nueva","Una tradición olvidada"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','Smartphones in the Classroom',
'In recent years, smartphones have become an essential tool for many teenagers. They use them to communicate with friends, take photos, listen to music, and access information. However, the use of smartphones in schools is a controversial topic. Some teachers and parents believe that mobile phones are a distraction in the classroom. Students may use them to chat or play games instead of paying attention to the lesson. They also argue that phones can be used for cheating during exams. For these reasons, several countries, like France, have banned smartphones in schools for students under fifteen. On the other hand, many educators see smartphones as a useful learning tool. With a phone, students can quickly look up information, translate words, watch educational videos, and use special apps for studying. Some schools have even introduced "bring your own device" programmes, where students use their phones during certain activities. The debate is far from over. The challenge is to find a balance: how can we use technology in a positive way without letting it interfere with learning and concentration?',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Por qué algunos profesores y padres están en contra de los móviles en clase?","opciones":["Porque son caros","Porque distraen y permiten copiar en exámenes","Porque dañan la vista","Porque no tienen batería"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué país ha prohibido los móviles en las escuelas para menores de quince años?","opciones":["España","Francia","Alemania","Italia"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cómo pueden ser útiles los móviles según otros educadores?","opciones":["Solo para hacer fotos","Para buscar información, traducir y usar apps educativas","Para llamar a casa","Para escuchar música"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cuál es el reto según el texto?","opciones":["Prohibir los móviles","Encontrar un equilibrio entre tecnología y concentración","Usar siempre los móviles","Cambiar todos los libros por móviles"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','Saving the Bees',
'Bees are tiny insects, but they play an enormous role in our ecosystem. They are responsible for pollinating most of the flowers and crops that humans need to survive. Without bees, we would not have apples, almonds, strawberries, coffee, or many other foods that we eat every day. Scientists estimate that one third of the food we consume depends directly or indirectly on bee pollination. Unfortunately, bee populations are in serious decline all over the world. The main reasons are the use of pesticides in agriculture, climate change, the loss of natural habitats, and certain diseases. To save the bees, many people are taking action. Some schools and families are creating small "bee-friendly" gardens with wild flowers where bees can find pollen. Beekeepers are working hard to protect their hives. Governments are also starting to ban dangerous pesticides. Even children can help by planting flowers on their balconies or learning about these amazing insects. Albert Einstein once said that if bees disappeared, humans would only have a few years left. Whether the quote is true or not, it shows the importance of these little workers.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Qué porcentaje de los alimentos depende de la polinización de las abejas?","opciones":["Una décima parte","Una cuarta parte","Una tercera parte","La mitad"],"correcta":2},{"pregunta":"¿Cuáles son las causas del descenso de las abejas?","opciones":["Solo el clima","Pesticidas, cambio climático, pérdida de hábitats y enfermedades","Los pájaros","La contaminación lumínica"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué pueden hacer los niños para ayudar?","opciones":["Comprar miel","Plantar flores en sus balcones","Capturar abejas","Construir colmenas"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué dijo Einstein sobre las abejas según el texto?","opciones":["Que no son importantes","Que si desaparecieran, a los humanos les quedarían pocos años","Que producen mucha miel","Que pican mucho"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','Halloween: An Ancient Festival',
'Halloween is celebrated every year on the thirty-first of October, especially in countries like the United States, Canada, Ireland, and the United Kingdom. Although today it is associated with costumes, sweets, and pumpkins, this festival has very ancient origins. It comes from an old Celtic celebration called Samhain, which marked the end of the harvest season and the beginning of winter. The Celts believed that on this night, the spirits of the dead returned to visit the world of the living. They lit big bonfires and wore costumes made of animal skins to scare the spirits away. When Irish people emigrated to America in the nineteenth century, they brought this tradition with them, and it gradually became the modern Halloween we know today. Now, children dress up as witches, ghosts, vampires, or superheroes and go from house to house saying "trick or treat" to receive sweets. People also decorate their houses with pumpkins called "jack-o''-lanterns", which have scary faces carved on them. Halloween is now one of the most popular festivals in the western world, and it is also celebrated more and more in countries like Spain.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿De qué celebración antigua proviene Halloween?","opciones":["Una romana","Una celta llamada Samhain","Una egipcia","Una vikinga"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Por qué los celtas se disfrazaban con pieles de animales?","opciones":["Para divertirse","Para asustar a los espíritus","Por moda","Para abrigarse"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Quiénes llevaron la tradición a América?","opciones":["Los británicos","Los irlandeses","Los franceses","Los alemanes"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cómo se llaman las calabazas decoradas?","opciones":["Pumpkin pies","Jack-o''-lanterns","Halloween balls","Ghost lamps"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','Plastic in the Oceans',
'Plastic pollution in the oceans has become one of the most serious environmental problems of our time. Every year, more than eight million tonnes of plastic end up in the sea. This rubbish comes mostly from the land, carried by rivers, wind, and rain. Plastic does not disappear: it breaks into tiny pieces called microplastics that can stay in the water for hundreds of years. Marine animals such as turtles, dolphins, whales, and seabirds often eat plastic by mistake. Some die because their stomachs become full of waste, while others get trapped in plastic bags or fishing nets. Scientists have also found microplastics inside fish that humans eat, which means that plastic can enter our food chain too. There are now huge "islands of plastic" floating in the oceans. The largest one, located in the Pacific Ocean, is called the Great Pacific Garbage Patch and it is bigger than France. To solve this problem, many countries have banned single-use plastic bags and straws. Each of us can also help by using reusable bottles, refusing plastic packaging, and recycling whenever possible.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Cuántas toneladas de plástico llegan al mar cada año?","opciones":["Un millón","Cinco millones","Más de ocho millones","Veinte millones"],"correcta":2},{"pregunta":"¿Qué son los microplásticos?","opciones":["Plásticos grandes","Pequeños trozos de plástico","Bolsas reutilizables","Botellas nuevas"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cómo se llama la mayor isla de plástico?","opciones":["Atlantic Trash Island","Great Pacific Garbage Patch","Indian Plastic Sea","Mediterranean Plastic Cloud"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué pueden hacer las personas para ayudar?","opciones":["Comprar más plástico","Usar botellas reutilizables y reciclar","Tirar la basura al mar","Comer menos pescado"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','The Story of Coca-Cola',
'Coca-Cola is one of the most famous brands in the world. The drink was invented in 1886 by an American pharmacist named John Pemberton in Atlanta, Georgia. Originally, Pemberton created it as a kind of medicine for headaches. He mixed coca leaves with kola nuts and other ingredients, and that is where the name comes from. At first, Coca-Cola was sold in pharmacies as a syrup that customers mixed with water. The recipe was a complete failure for medicine, but people loved the taste. A few years later, an entrepreneur called Asa Candler bought the formula and began to sell Coca-Cola in glass bottles. He invested huge amounts of money in advertising, and the product became popular all over the United States. During the twentieth century, Coca-Cola spread to almost every country in the world. Today, it is sold in more than two hundred countries and millions of people drink it every day. The company has kept its original recipe a secret for more than a century, and only a few people are supposed to know the full list of ingredients. Coca-Cola has become a symbol of American culture worldwide.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Quién inventó la Coca-Cola?","opciones":["Asa Candler","John Pemberton","Henry Ford","Walt Disney"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Para qué se creó originalmente?","opciones":["Como refresco","Como medicina para el dolor de cabeza","Como zumo","Como bebida deportiva"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿En cuántos países se vende hoy?","opciones":["En cien","En doscientos","En más de doscientos","En cincuenta"],"correcta":2},{"pregunta":"¿Qué se mantiene en secreto?","opciones":["El precio","La receta original","El logo","La fábrica"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','Self-Driving Cars',
'For many years, self-driving cars seemed like an idea from a science-fiction film. Today, they are becoming a reality. Several technology companies, including Google, Tesla, and Apple, have been working on this innovation for over a decade. A self-driving car uses cameras, sensors, GPS, and artificial intelligence to detect everything around it: other vehicles, pedestrians, traffic lights, and road signs. The car can decide when to brake, turn, or accelerate without any help from the driver. Supporters of this technology believe self-driving cars will make our roads safer because most accidents are caused by human errors such as distractions, tiredness, or speeding. They could also reduce traffic in big cities and help people who cannot drive, like the elderly or disabled. However, there are still many concerns. What happens if a self-driving car has a serious accident? Who is responsible: the owner, the manufacturer, or the software developer? There are also worries about cybersecurity, because these vehicles could be hacked. Despite these challenges, experts predict that fully autonomous cars will be common on our streets within the next twenty years.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Qué tecnologías usan los coches autónomos?","opciones":["Solo cámaras","Cámaras, sensores, GPS e inteligencia artificial","Solo radio","Mapas en papel"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Por qué los defensores creen que serán más seguros?","opciones":["Porque son más rápidos","Porque la mayoría de accidentes son por errores humanos","Porque son más bonitos","Porque cuestan más"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cuál es una preocupación importante?","opciones":["El color del coche","La ciberseguridad y la responsabilidad en accidentes","El precio del combustible","El tamaño del coche"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué predicen los expertos?","opciones":["Que nunca funcionarán","Que serán comunes en los próximos veinte años","Que solo los usarán los ricos","Que serán prohibidos"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','The Tradition of Carnival',
'Carnival is one of the most colourful and exciting festivals in the world. It is celebrated in many countries, especially those with a Catholic tradition, in the days before Lent. The most famous carnivals take place in Rio de Janeiro in Brazil, in Venice in Italy, and in the Canary Islands and Cádiz in Spain. Each city has its own traditions, but all of them share music, dance, costumes, and a happy atmosphere. The Carnival of Rio is the biggest in the world. Every year, samba schools spend months preparing extraordinary parades, with thousands of dancers wearing spectacular costumes. The Carnival of Venice, on the other hand, is famous for its elegant masks and old-fashioned costumes inspired by the eighteenth century. People walk through the narrow streets of the city like characters from another time. In Spain, the Carnival of Cádiz is known for its humorous songs called "chirigotas", which often make jokes about politics and current events. Carnival is more than a party: it is a moment when people forget their daily worries and enjoy life. The streets fill with laughter, music, and creativity.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Cuándo se celebra el Carnaval?","opciones":["En Navidad","En los días anteriores a la Cuaresma","En verano","En Pascua"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué Carnaval es el más grande del mundo?","opciones":["El de Venecia","El de Río de Janeiro","El de Cádiz","El de Tenerife"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Por qué es famoso el Carnaval de Venecia?","opciones":["Por las chirigotas","Por sus máscaras elegantes y trajes del siglo XVIII","Por su comida","Por su tamaño"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Qué son las chirigotas?","opciones":["Bailes","Canciones humorísticas con bromas sobre política","Trajes","Comidas típicas"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb),
('ingles','eso','{3}','Virtual Reality',
'Virtual reality, often called VR, is a technology that allows users to experience a digital world as if it were real. With special glasses or headsets, people can move, look around, and interact with the virtual environment. Virtual reality was invented several decades ago, but it has become much more popular in recent years thanks to faster computers and better graphics. Today, VR is mostly known for video games, where players can feel like they are inside the game. However, this technology has many other interesting uses. In medicine, doctors and surgeons use virtual reality to practise complicated operations without any risk for real patients. In education, students can visit ancient Rome, explore the human body, or travel to outer space without leaving the classroom. The military uses VR to train soldiers in dangerous situations, and architects can show their clients exactly how a new building will look before it is constructed. Some psychologists even use virtual reality to help people overcome their fears, such as the fear of flying or of public speaking. As technology continues to improve, virtual reality will surely become an even more important part of our lives.',
'[{"pregunta":"¿Qué se necesita para usar la realidad virtual?","opciones":["Un teléfono normal","Gafas o cascos especiales","Un libro","Un televisor"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Para qué la usan los médicos?","opciones":["Para curar enfermedades","Para practicar operaciones complicadas sin riesgo","Para descansar","Para jugar"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cómo ayuda la VR en la educación según el texto?","opciones":["Sustituye a los profesores","Permite visitar lugares y explorar sin salir del aula","Da puntos extra","Hace los exámenes"],"correcta":1},{"pregunta":"¿Cómo la usan algunos psicólogos?","opciones":["Para hacer reír","Para ayudar a superar miedos","Para enseñar idiomas","Para jugar al fútbol"],"correcta":1}]'::jsonb);

